highlights.text: Taylor Swift has the most spots on Top Songs USA. “Cruel Summer” is the highest at #36.
“What Christmas Means To Me” by Stevie Wonder is the biggest gainer on Top Songs USA, up 80 spots at #92.
“Christmas (Baby Please Come Home)” by Michael Bublé is the highest new entry on Top Songs USA at #160.
“No Role Modelz” by J. Cole has been on Top Songs USA the longest, at 188 weeks straight.
